bilingual.target: 我想帮助无家可归的人。
她收养了一个无家可归的流浪儿。
无家可归的人们需要一个庇护所。
他们帮助了那个无家可归的花子。

bilingual.source: We can donate food to the homeless.
bilingual.target: 我们可以布施食物给无家可归的人。

bilingual.source: She is dishing out soup to the homeless.
bilingual.target: 她正在给无家可归的人分发汤。

bilingual.source: She decided to take in the homeless people.
bilingual.target: 她决定收容那些无家可归的人。

bilingual.source: Many homeless people go begging in the city.
bilingual.target: 许多无家可归的人在城市里行乞。

bilingual.source: There are many homeless people in this city.
bilingual.target: 这个城市有很多无家可归的人。
他们为无家可归的孩子提供了庇护所。

list.abstract: 《Homeless》是国内首本也是唯一一本单亲情感类电子杂志，以治愈、温暖、坚强为关键字，试图给孩子们带来一种别样的感受。
Homeless是2011年法国达人秀冠军Marina Kaye于2014年发行的单曲。此单曲被收录在Homeless EP和Marina首专Fearless中。2014-2015年登顶法国SNEP排行榜。

yingyinNormal.en: And Raj and I are volunteering at the soup kitchen, feeding food to the homeless.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我跟拉杰要去粥棚当自愿者，给无家可归的人发食物。

yingyinNormal.en: Who's the homeless person on the couch?
What type of people live there? Junkies, whores, homeless. Actors.
yingyinNormal.zh: "描述附近居民？"毒虫，妓女，流浪汉。演员。

yingyinNormal.en: Even the homeless lady on the bus had a new barrette.
yingyinNormal.zh: 就连公车上的流浪女也有个新发夹。

yingyinNormal.en: So is she, like, homeless, or framing him for a crime?
yingyinNormal.zh: 所以这妞是无家可归还是要栽赃陷害？

yingyinNormal.en: Molly Hooper and some of my homeless network and that's all.
yingyinNormal.zh: 茉莉胡珀 还有我的流浪汉消息网的几个人。

yingyinNormal.en: That covers anything from farting in bed to killing a homeless guy.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你说的这范围广的可以从被窝里放屁延伸到杀害流浪汉。

yingyinNormal.en: I personally have shooed a homeless man away from peeing on that shrine twice.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我亲自赶走了一个流浪汉不让他往神龛上撒尿，赶了两次啊。

yingyinNormal.en: A partially eaten piece of pumpkin pie from a homeless shelter, with Elon Musk, you bet I do!
yingyinNormal.zh: 跟埃隆·马斯克在收容所一起分享被吃过的南瓜派，我当然愿意。

yingyinNormal.en: I have seen how you treat your friends! We came to you once, starving, homeless, seeking your help.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我看到过你怎样对待盟友，我们找到你，饥肠辘辘，无家可归，渴求你的帮助。

yingyinNormal.en: What? Yeah, it was just sitting on the street. I paid a homeless guy ten bucks to help me get it up here.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你说什么？就是说呀，这椅子就被丢在路上，我给了个流浪汉十块钱让他帮我把这张椅子搬上来的。

yingyinNormal.en: Ross, Ross, you have no idea what this means to me. I mean, I mean I was gonna be homeless. You just saved me. You're my hero.
yingyinNormal.zh: 罗斯，这对我太重要了，我差点就要流落街头，你救了我，你是我的英雄。

yingyinNormal.en: Khadijah had attended twelve schools in twelve years, living out of garbage bags amongst pimps, prostitutes and drug dealers, homeless, going into department stores Wal-Mart in the morning to bathe herself, so that she wouldn't smelling in front of her classmates.
yingyinNormal.zh: 赫蒂彻在12年中读过12所学校，和皮条客、妓女与毒贩生活在一起，居无定所。每当大清早时，她会去沃尔玛商场洗漱，以免让同学闻到自己身上的臭味。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>

examination_example.sentence: When one looks at the photographs of the gardens created by the <highlight>homeless</highlight>, it strikes one that,  these gardens speak of various other fundamental urges.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当人们看到这些由无家可归者创造的花园的照片时，会突然想到，这些花园反映了各种其他的基本需求。

examination_example.sentence: The compositions represent attempts to call forth the spirit of plant and animal life through an arrangement of materials and a frequent presence of stuffed animals.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 借助材料的安排布置和频繁出现的填充毛绒动物，这些作品试图唤起动植物的生命力。

examination_example.sentence: The <highlight>homeless</highlight> gardens introduce form into an urban environment where it either didn't exist or was not discernible as such.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 无家可归者花园将形式引入了一个城市环境，在那里它要么不存在，要么看不出来。
